FBIS4-62864 "drsov097_r_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 Azerbaijan `Comparative Lull' in Zone of Hostilities `Comparative Lull' in Zone of Hostilities NC1805194194 Baku AZERTAC in English 1620 GMT 18 May 94 NC1805194194 Baku AZERTAC English BFN [Text] Baku, 18 May (AZERTAC)--A comparative lull is maintained in the zone of hostilities, the Azerbaijani Defence Ministry reported today. However, the Azeri Army's positions have come under the mortar and tank fire in some sectors of the front. Thus the village of Sadarak in the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic was shelled last night. One soldier was injured. According to the Defence Ministry, the Azerbaijani Army has not yet opened retaliatory fire, thus proposing the Armenians to observe the truce.
